    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Term used in maritime commerce to signify the damage or expenses resulting from the perils of marine navigation such as damage caused by storm, collision or cargo shifting. It also implies partial, as distinguished from total, loss. To be distinguished from 'general average' which refers to damage caused in shipsaving situations.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
